            <div type="edition" xml:space="preserve"><head>Text</head><ab><lb n="1"/>
                In <expan><abbr>h</abbr><ex>onorem</ex></expan> <expan><abbr>d</abbr><ex>omus</ex></expan> <expan><abbr>d</abbr><ex>ivinae</ex></expan> Deo Invic<lb break="no" n="2"/>to <expan><abbr>M</abbr><ex>ithrae</ex></expan> <expan><abbr>C</abbr><ex>aius</ex></expan> Celsinius <lb n="3"/>Matutinus <expan><abbr>veter</abbr><ex>anus</ex></expan> <lb n="4"/><expan><abbr>leg</abbr><ex>ionis</ex></expan> VIII <expan><abbr>Aug</abbr><ex>ustae</ex></expan> <del rend="erasure">Alex</del><lb break="no" n="5"/><del rend="erasure">andrianae</del> typ<lb break="no" n="6"/>um de suo <expan><abbr>repinx</abbr><ex>it</ex></expan>
            </ab></div>
            <div type="commentary">
                <p>Aus dem selben Kontext eine weitere, fast gleich aussehende Tafel mit nahezu identischer Inschrift erhalten (HD030724). Im mehrere Fragmente gebrochen. Bei Cubaynes kein Hinweis auf die Tilgung.</p>
            </div>
